  "writeup": "The Buffalo Bills made a definitive statement as their new Highmark Stadium takes shape, announcing that O.J. Simpson will not be honored among the franchise's all-time greats — a decision that has sparked significant discussion among fans and media alike. Meanwhile, names of Bills legends are beginning to appear around the new venue, signaling an exciting new chapter for the franchise. On the roster front, Bills Mafia and analysts are zeroing in on the team's offensive playmaker depth as a potential weakness, with ESPN ranking Buffalo near the bottom of NFL offensive playmaker groups heading into 2026. There's also buzz around late free agent signings reshaping the depth chart, including concerns about whether the CJ Gardner-Johnson deal will pan out. Off the field, Seneca Resorts & Casinos signed on as a Founding Partner of Highmark Stadium, further cementing the new venue's growing corporate footprint.",
